<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="Hypoglycaemia">
  <data key="d0">Hypoglycaemia</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Hypoglycaemia is a condition where blood sugar levels drop too low, often resulting in symptoms such as dizziness and confusion.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypoglycaemia is a condition characterized by abnormally low blood sugar levels, which can occur in diabetic patients, especially those on insulin.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypoglycaemia is defined as an abnormally low concentration of glucose in the blood, often affecting diabetes patients and leading to various symptoms and complications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849992</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ketoacidosis">
  <data key="d0">Ketoacidosis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Ketoacidosis is a serious complication of diabetes mainly affecting people with type 1 diabetes, resulting from the body's breakdown of fatty acids and production of ketones.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849992</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Blood Glucose Targets">
  <data key="d0">Blood Glucose Targets</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Blood glucose targets refer to individualized goals for blood sugar levels that diabetic patients aim to maintain to prevent complications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849992</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Emergency Medical Personnel">
  <data key="d0">Emergency Medical Personnel</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Emergency Medical Personnel are healthcare workers trained to respond to medical emergencies, including the recognition and treatment of hypoglycaemia.&lt;SEP&gt;Emergency medical personnel are healthcare workers trained to provide immediate treatment in medical emergencies, including the recognition and management of hypoglycaemia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849992</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Glucagon">
  <data key="d0">Glucagon</data>
  <data key="d1">medication</data>
  <data key="d2">Glucagon is a hormone used to treat severe hypoglycaemia, often administered in emergencies to raise blood glucose levels.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849992</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Type 1 Diabetes">
  <data key="d0">Type 1 Diabetes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Type 1 diabetes is an autoimmune condition where the pancreas produces little or no insulin, requiring lifelong insulin therapy.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 1 Diabetes is a form of diabetes where the body does not produce insulin, leading to high blood sugar levels and complications like ketoacidosis.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849992</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Type 2 Diabetes">
  <data key="d0">Type 2 Diabetes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Type 2 diabetes is a form of diabetes mellitus that is increasingly diagnosed in younger populations and is linked to obesity and inactivity.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 diabetes is a form of diabetes that often develops at a young age and is characterized by insulin resistance.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 diabetes is a chronic condition characterized by insulin resistance and high blood sugar levels, often leading to serious health complications.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 diabetes is a metabolic disorder characterized by insulin resistance and relative insulin deficiency, often manageable with lifestyle changes and medications.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 Diabetes is a form of diabetes where the body is resistant to insulin or does not produce enough insulin, making it more prone to hyperglycaemic hyperosmolar state.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 Diabetes is a more common form of diabetes that typically develops in adults and is often associated with obesity and sedentary lifestyle.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5384df975133ef2a52113cd3ca0f897e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f15f59b3ff05825a61f252ed8f9a74e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56d9ff3515afac60e7566e41837249a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849992</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sulfonylureas">
  <data key="d0">Sulfonylureas</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Sulfonylureas are a type of insulin secretagogues commonly prescribed for diabetes management.&lt;SEP&gt;Sulfonylureas are a class of oral hypoglycaemic agents that stimulate insulin secretion from the pancreas but may induce hypoglycaemia.&lt;SEP&gt;Sulfonylureas are a class of oral medications used to treat type 2 diabetes by increasing insulin sensitivity and production.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849992</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Acidosis">
  <data key="d0">Acidosis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Acidosis is a condition characterized by increased acidity in the blood, which can be associated with diabetes complications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849992</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Brown Urine">
  <data key="d0">Brown Urine</data>
  <data key="d1">symptom</data>
  <data key="d2">Brown urine is a potential indicator of diabetic ketoacidosis or other serious health issues requiring medical attention.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849992</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Myocardial Infarction">
  <data key="d0">Myocardial Infarction</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Myocardial infarction refers to a medical condition commonly known as a heart attack, characterized by the interruption of blood supply to a part of the heart.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849993</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Insulin Resistance">
  <data key="d0">Insulin Resistance</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Insulin resistance is a condition associated with several health issues, including diabetes and other metabolic disorders.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin resistance is a metabolic condition where the body's cells fail to respond effectively to insulin, leading to increased blood sugar levels.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin resistance is a condition in which cells do not respond well to insulin, contributing to higher blood sugar levels and complications in diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849993</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dyslipidaemia">
  <data key="d0">Dyslipidaemia</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Dyslipidaemia refers to abnormal lipid levels in the blood, which can have various secondary causes that need to be ruled out.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia is a condition characterized by abnormal amounts of lipids in the blood, often associated with metabolic disorders such as diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia is a medical condition characterized by abnormal cholesterol levels, which is associated with increased cardiovascular risk in individuals with type 2 diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia is an abnormal amount of lipids in the blood, often requiring management strategies such as controlling LDL and triglyceride levels.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia is a condition associated with abnormal lipid levels in the blood, common in individuals with diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia refers to abnormal lipid levels, a health concern that can complicate diabetes management.&lt;SEP&gt;Dyslipidaemia refers to an imbalance of lipids in the blood, which can be managed through a healthy lifestyle including diet, weight loss, and exercise.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8361af576f7e73b0bd2ea813976f60b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849993</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Obesity">
  <data key="d0">Obesity</data>
  <data key="d1">condition</data>
  <data key="d2">Obesity is a medical condition characterized by excessive body fat, contributing to various health issues, including diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity is a medical condition characterized by excessive body fat, increasing the risk of various health issues, including cardiovascular disease.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity is a significant health issue characterized by excessive body fat, commonly associated with insulin resistance and diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity is a condition assessed by body mass index, increasing the risk of dyslipidaemia and insulin resistance in individuals with type 2 diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity is a significant risk factor for developing diabetes and complicates its management.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity, particularly abdominal obesity, increases the risk of atherosclerosis and is often associated with diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity is recognized as a major risk factor for diabetes, hypertension, and cardiovascular diseases, necessitating awareness and preventive measures in the community.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2173942c84747feba52cff952903a7f5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849993</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Blood Pressure">
  <data key="d0">Blood Pressure</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Blood pressure is the force of blood against the walls of arteries, with elevated levels indicating hypertension.&lt;SEP&gt;Blood pressure is the force of blood against the walls of arteries, measured in millimeters of mercury (mmHg), indicating cardiovascular health.&lt;SEP&gt;Blood pressure levels should be monitored regularly in diabetic patients, with target levels set below &lt;130/80 mmHg.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849993</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Antihypertensive Therapy">
  <data key="d0">Antihypertensive Therapy</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Antihypertensive therapy refers to treatment strategies aimed at lowering high blood pressure to prevent related health complications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849993</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Lipid-Lowering Therapy">
  <data key="d0">Lipid-Lowering Therapy</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Lipid-lowering therapy involves medications or dietary treatments aimed at reducing lipid levels in the blood to decrease cardiovascular risk.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849993</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Antiplatelet Therapy">
  <data key="d0">Antiplatelet Therapy</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Antiplatelet therapy uses medications to prevent blood clots by inhibiting platelet aggregation, reducing the risk of cardiovascular events.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849993</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hypertension Optimal Treatment (HOT) Trial">
  <data key="d0">Hypertension Optimal Treatment (HOT) Trial</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The Hypertension Optimal Treatment (HOT) trial is a significant clinical study assessing the effects of blood pressure reduction on cardiovascular outcomes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849994</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study (UKPDS)">
  <data key="d0">United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study (UKPDS)</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study (UKPDS) is a major clinical study that explored the management and treatment of type 2 diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849994</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Appropriate Blood Pressure Control in Diabetes (ABCD) Study">
  <data key="d0">Appropriate Blood Pressure Control in Diabetes (ABCD) Study</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The Appropriate Blood Pressure Control in Diabetes (ABCD) study investigates the implications of managing blood pressure in diabetic patients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849994</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fasting Lipid Profile">
  <data key="d0">Fasting Lipid Profile</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A fasting lipid profile is a blood test measuring lipid levels after fasting, recommended for monitoring patients with diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849994</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hypertensive Heart Disease">
  <data key="d0">Hypertensive Heart Disease</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Hypertensive heart disease refers to complications that arise from uncontrolled hypertension, affecting heart health and function.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849994</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cardiovascular Mortality">
  <data key="d0">Cardiovascular Mortality</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Cardiovascular mortality refers to death caused by heart-related conditions, often linked to factors such as hypertension and diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849994</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Atherogenic Properties">
  <data key="d0">Atherogenic Properties</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Atherogenic properties refer to characteristics of substances that promote the formation of fatty deposits in arteries, increasing cardiovascular risk.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849994</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Postprandial Lipaemia">
  <data key="d0">Postprandial Lipaemia</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Postprandial lipaemia is characterized by elevated lipid levels in the blood after eating, which can be a risk factor in dyslipidaemia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849994</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Diabetes">
  <data key="d0">Diabetes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Diabetes is a chronic condition that occurs when the body does not properly process food for use as energy, often related to hyperglycaemia and insulin resistance.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetes is a medical condition characterized by high blood sugar levels due to insulin resistance or insufficient insulin production.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetes is a chronic condition that affects how the body processes glucose, leading to various complications such as infections and atherosclerosis.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetes is a chronic condition characterized by high blood sugar levels and has various complications, including neuropathy and increased risk of lower-limb amputations.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetes is a chronic health condition characterized by high blood sugar and associated with various complications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55d2691a8c714949752d249721fec5e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2173942c84747feba52cff952903a7f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849994</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Diabetic Retinopathy">
  <data key="d0">Diabetic Retinopathy</data>
  <data key="d1">condition</data>
  <data key="d2">Diabetic retinopathy is a serious eye condition associated with diabetes, leading to blindness and visual impairment in many adults.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849994</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Atherosclerosis">
  <data key="d0">Atherosclerosis</data>
  <data key="d1">condition</data>
  <data key="d2">Atherosclerosis is a common macrovascular complication of diabetes, increasing the risk of cardiovascular diseases and premature death.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849994</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hyperglycaemia">
  <data key="d0">Hyperglycaemia</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Hyperglycaemia refers to high blood sugar levels, which can occur in various forms of diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Hyperglycaemia is a condition characterized by elevated blood glucose levels, commonly associated with diabetes and the metabolic syndrome.&lt;SEP&gt;Hyperglycaemia refers to high blood sugar levels, which can promote atherosclerosis and other complications in diabetics.&lt;SEP&gt;Hyperglycaemia refers to elevated blood glucose levels that impact nerve structure and function, potentially leading to neuropathy.&lt;SEP&gt;Hyperglycaemia is a condition defined by elevated blood glucose levels, often associated with diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd4cfbed43aa26af0eef694fecac2177&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0748670b42b0f4e0b2ed9c5ce62d54e7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849995</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Urinary Tract Infections">
  <data key="d0">Urinary Tract Infections</data>
  <data key="d1">condition</data>
  <data key="d2">Urinary tract infections are more common in diabetics, especially following bladder instrumentation and due to neurogenic bladder issues.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849995</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Patient Management Protocol">
  <data key="d0">Patient Management Protocol</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The patient management protocol outlines steps for managing hyperglycaemic crises in diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849995</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chronic Painless Infection">
  <data key="d0">Chronic Painless Infection</data>
  <data key="d1">condition</data>
  <data key="d2">Chronic painless infection may lead to the destruction of a neuropathic and/or ischaemic foot in individuals with diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769849995</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Diabetic Ketoacidosis">
  <data key="d0">Diabetic Ketoacidosis</data>
  <data key="d1">condition</data>
  <data key="d2">Diabetic ketoacidosis is a severe complication of diabetes characterized by high blood sugar and the presence of ketones in the urine.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetic ketoacidosis is a serious complication that can be precipitated by infections in individuals with diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
