<node id="Screening Programme">
  <data key="d0">Screening Programme</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Screening Programme refers to organized efforts to identify individuals at risk for diabetes and ensure appropriate follow-up and care.&lt;SEP&gt;A screening programme is a strategy used to regularly assess diabetic patients for risks of developing foot ulcers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-25fb88c8ed14936954356d104de095d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55d2691a8c714949752d249721fec5e7</data>
