  <data key="d0">Ophthalmologist</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The ophthalmologist conducts annual retinal screenings for patients with diabetes to monitor for signs of diabetic retinopathy.&lt;SEP&gt;An ophthalmologist is a medical doctor specializing in eye and vision care, including the diagnosis and treatment of eye diseases and conditions.</data>
