<node id="Aldose Reductase Inhibitors">
  <data key="d0">Aldose Reductase Inhibitors</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Aldose reductase inhibitors are a class of drugs that have not demonstrated efficacy in preventing the development or progression of retinopathy in humans.&lt;SEP&gt;Aldose reductase inhibitors are medications that inhibit the polyol pathway, potentially preventing diabetic neuropathy.&lt;SEP&gt;Aldose reductase inhibitors are therapeutic agents that should be investigated for their potential in treating neuropathy.</data>
