<node id="World Health Organization">
  <data key="d0">World Health Organization</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The World Health Organization is a specialized agency of the United Nations responsible for international public health and has published this document on diabetes care.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization is a global health agency that provides estimates and advises on public health challenges, including diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization is the global governing body that oversees health guidelines, including those for diabetes prevention and control.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization is a global health agency that conducted a survey assessing diabetes prevention strategies in Eastern Mediterranean countries.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization (WHO) is a specialized agency of the United Nations focused on global public health, authoring reports relevant to diabetes management.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization is a specialized agency of the United Nations responsible for public health and global health issues, involved in various diabetes-related initiatives and reports.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization is an international public health agency involved in reporting related to diabetes prevention and control.</data>
