  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The Eastern Mediterranean Region is a geographical area experiencing increasing diabetes prevalence and related health issues.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region encompasses several countries and has a diverse population with varying diabetes prevalence rates.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is a geographic area with specific health concerns regarding diabetes prevalence and management.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is included among the WHO regions highlighted in the context of diabetes management and prevention.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is mentioned in relation to screening recommendations for type 2 diabetes in children.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is noted for a rising prevalence of type 2 diabetes among its population.</data>
