<node id="Gestational Diabetes">
  <data key="d0">Gestational Diabetes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Gestational diabetes refers to diabetes that develops during pregnancy and has been redefined to include various subcategories.&lt;SEP&gt;Gestational diabetes is a form of carbohydrate intolerance with onset during pregnancy, affecting glucose levels.&lt;SEP&gt;Gestational diabetes is a form of diabetes that occurs during pregnancy, usually resolving after childbirth.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c</data>
