  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Oral Glucose Tolerance Test (OGTT) is a diagnostic procedure used to determine if gestational diabetes is present.&lt;SEP&gt;OGTT (Oral Glucose Tolerance Test) is a diagnostic test used to assess how well the body processes glucose and can help identify individuals with impaired glucose tolerance (IGT).</data>
