<node id="Insulin">
  <data key="d0">Insulin</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Insulin is a hormone produced by the pancreas that regulates glucose levels in the blood and is crucial for individuals with diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin is a hormone that regulates blood glucose levels and is crucial in diabetes management.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin is a hormone used to manage diabetes, with various types having specific onset, peak, and duration times.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin is a hormone that consistently lowers triglycerides in poorly controlled patients and may improve glycaemic control.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin is a hormone that regulates blood glucose levels, often used by diabetes patients to manage their condition.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
