<node id="Type 1 Diabetes Mellitus">
  <data key="d0">Type 1 Diabetes Mellitus</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Type 1 diabetes mellitus requires insulin for survival and is primarily due to pancreatic islet beta-cell destruction.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 1 Diabetes Mellitus is an autoimmune condition where the body's immune system attacks insulin-producing beta cells, requiring insulin for survival.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 1 diabetes mellitus is an autoimmune condition where the pancreas produces little to no insulin, often requiring strict monitoring and management.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 1 diabetes mellitus is a form of diabetes that currently does not have conclusive prevention methods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56d9ff3515afac60e7566e41837249a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51</data>
