  <data key="d0">Diabetic Nephropathy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Diabetic nephropathy refers to kidney disease caused by diabetes, being the most common cause of renal failure in diabetic patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetic nephropathy is a complication of diabetes characterized by kidney damage due to prolonged high blood sugar levels.</data>
