<node id="Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus">
  <data key="d0">Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus is a prevalent form of diabetes characterized by insulin resistance and inadequate insulin secretion. This condition may or may not necessitate insulin treatment, depending on the individual circumstances. It is increasingly observed in children and adolescents, often associated with rising rates of childhood obesity. 

Individuals with Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus typically experience high blood sugar levels and are at risk for various severe health complications if the condition goes unmanaged. It is primarily influenced by lifestyle factors, making it a significant public health concern. 

Prevention of Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus can be achieved through lifestyle modifications and primary prevention strategies, emphasizing the importance of healthy dietary practices and regular physical activity. Effective management of the condition may also involve lifestyle interventions, which can help maintain blood sugar levels and improve overall health.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56d9ff3515afac60e7566e41837249a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2173942c84747feba52cff952903a7f5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769850004</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
