<node id="Aspirin Therapy">
  <data key="d0">Aspirin Therapy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Aspirin therapy involves the use of aspirin as a secondary or primary prevention method for cardiovascular disease, particularly in diabetic patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Aspirin therapy involves the use of aspirin (75–162 mg/day) for the prevention and management of cardiovascular disease in at-risk patients, particularly those with diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
